  "spec_link": "https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/1562",
  "api_spec": true,
  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": "Interop: Given the developers' support in the github discussion and the easy resolution in the CSWWG, we expect other major browsers to implement this feature in near future.\n\nCompat: To maintain the backward compatibility for the scroll methods, we would avoid rejecting the returned Promises (as much as possible). This is because unhandled Promise rejections are treated as exceptions, which could fail any JS callers that assume that those methods succeed unconditionally.",
